{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, it is interesting to note that the MCC is improved as the training synthetic data is incremented, accomplishing a satisfactory performance (MCC higher than 0.40) by using 100 and 500 augmented data after the iteration number 15.",
    "On other hand, the model's performance evaluating the training dataset (Fig. 3B) is already satisfactory even without implementing any synthetic data (black line).",
    "This is expected since the same dataset was already seen by the deep neural network during the fine-tuning process.",
    "Additional information related to the confusion matrix used for calculating the test MCC at 15 epochs for both 100 and 500 synthetic data can be found in the supplementary information (Table SI 1 and Table SI 2).",
    "The measurement of the loss function was performed aiming to elucidate the effect of the implemented data augmentation strategy on the classifier's performance in terms of underfitting as well as overfitting."
  ]
}